MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: Perodua, TRC Synergy, TechnoDex, Mobif, Atis

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-05-03T21:14:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/malaysia-daybook-perodua-trc-synergy-technodex-mobif-atis.html
Perusahaan Otomobil Kedua Sdn., the
Malaysian automaker better known as Perodua, will hold a
briefing on its operations at 10:30 a.m. in  Kuala Lumpur ,
following disruptions to parts supplies from  Japan  after the
country’s earthquake and tsunami.  Perodua, which counts Daihatsu Motor Co., UMW Holdings Bhd.
and MBM Resources Bhd. among its shareholders, sources as much
as 10 percent of its engine parts from Japan for three models,
Managing Director Aminar Rashid Salleh told reporters on March
14.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* TRC Synergy Bhd. (TRC MK) won 45 million-ringgit construction
contract from Boustead Penang Shipyard Sdn., according to a
company statement.
* TechnoDex Bhd. (TDEX MK), a Malaysian software company, said
Priharta Development Sdn. ceased being a substantial shareholder
after selling 11.4 million shares in open market at average 7
sen each.
* Mobif Bhd. (MBF MK) said its shares to be suspended from May
10 until further notice after failing to submit 2010 audited
accounts on time.
* Fitters Diversified Bhd. (FIT MK)) said its shares to be
suspended from May 10 until further notice after failing to
submit audited accounts on time.
* Atis Corp. (ATIS MK) said its shares would be suspended from
May 10 until further notice after failing to submit audited
accounts on time.
* Golden Plus Holding Bhd. (GPH MK) said it was given five days
to submit audited accounts or risk having its shares suspended.  MARKETS:
*  Malaysia ’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index fell 0.2 percent.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index dropped 0.7 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  was unchanged.
* Palm oil July-delivery futures advanced 0.03 percent to 3,271
ringgit a metric ton.  BTV HIGHLIGHTS (KL times):
*6:30am David Blanchflower, Dartmouth
*8:10am Tim Schroeders, Pengana Capital Management
*9:50am Mike Elliott, Ernst and Young
*9:40am Azran Osman Rani, AirAsia X CEO
